{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" = "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSpawnChildSetupFunc","text":"GSpawnChildSetupFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On POSIX platforms, the function is called in the child after GLib"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"has performed all the setup it plans to perform, but before calling","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"exec()"},{"type":"text","text":". Actions taken in this function will only affect the child,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not the parent.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Windows, the function is called in the parent. Its usefulness on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Windows is thus questionable. In many cases executing the child setup"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function in the parent can have ill effects, and you should be very"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"careful when porting software to Windows that uses child setup"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"functions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"However, even on POSIX, you are extremely limited in what you can","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"safely do from a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SpawnChildSetupFunc"},{"type":"text","text":", because any mutexes that were"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"held by other threads in the parent process at the time of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fork()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will still be locked in the child process, and they will never be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unlocked (since the threads that held them don’t exist in the child)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"POSIX allows only async-signal-safe functions (see "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signal(7)"},{"type":"text","text":") to be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"called in the child between ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fork()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"exec()"},{"type":"text","text":", which drastically limits"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the usefulness of child setup functions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In particular, it is not safe to call any function which may","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"malloc()"},{"type":"text","text":", which includes POSIX functions such as "},{"code":"setenv()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If you need to set up the child environment differently from","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the parent, you should use "},{"code":"g_get_environ()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"g_environ_setenv()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_environ_unsetenv()"},{"type":"text","text":", and then pass the complete environment"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"list to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn..."},{"text":" function.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/spawnchildsetupfunc"]}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Type Alias","role":"symbol","title":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","symbolKind":"typealias","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib19SpawnChildSetupFunca","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","kind":"identifier"}]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SpawnChildSetupFunc"},"abstract":[{"text":"Specifies the type of the setup function passed to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_async()"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_sync()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"g_spawn_async_with_pipes()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", which can, in very"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"limited ways, be used to affect the child’s execution."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SpawnChildSetupFunc":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/spawnchildsetupfunc","abstract":[{"text":"Specifies the type of the setup function passed to ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_spawn_async()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_sync()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"g_spawn_async_with_pipes()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", which can, in very"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"limited ways, be used to affect the child’s execution."}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SpawnChildSetupFunc","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib"}}}